      neutralCase: "The market may remain volatile, with oil prices fluctuating within a range as geopolitical tensions simmer without full-scale conflict. India\'s strong domestic growth could partially offset the impact of elevated, but not runaway, oil prices. The RBI might adopt a measured approach to monetary policy, balancing inflation control with growth support, leading to a sideways or range-bound performance for Indian equities.",
